defaultWhat defaultimpact defaultdo defaultwedefault defaultanticipate overdefault the coming months for defaultour customersdefault?default default&#xa0;defaultIn our area the private rented sector is limited and 
defaultinsecure, so the opportunities for people to downsize into this sector are both severely limited and undesirable. 
defaultResearch in this area shows for the area that Aragon operates in (
defaultCentral  B
defaultedfordshire), 
defaultthe average private rent for a two
default bedroom property is £156.13 per week, which is £29.18 per week above the Local Housing Allowance for the majority of the region. This means that should our tenants move to such properties, they face an average 18.6% shortfall, 
defaultdespite
default occupying properties of the correct size. This means both a larger shortfall for tenants and higher Housing Benefit awards; the result is that costs are both higher for tenants and Local Authorities. Therefore, moving to the private rented sector is simply not a viable option in our region.
default  The same is true for those living in South Northants Homes
default’
default area.
default&#xa0;
defaultFurthermore, 
defaultas a G
defaultroup 
defaultwe 
defaultdo not have enough smaller units to rehouse all of those affected by the 
defaultunder-occupancy charge
default, so over time, we anticipate that our most vulnerable tenants will no longer have the capacity to maintain their tenancies, leading to evictions, increased levels of personal debt and the resulting pressures on public/private services, such as 
defaultfood banks
default, clothing banks, 
defaultGUHG’s 
defaultand the Council
defaults’
default support teams and statutory services such as social services.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe councils
default’
default DHP budget
defaults will soon be spent, and 
defaultour tenants currently maintaining their tenancies in this way will need to find another option.  There are limited options to move and as such, we anticipate that these families will quickly get into serious debt, both housing and otherwise
default resulting in
default a catastrophic impact on some households. The DHP scheme merely offers temp
defaultorary respite from benefit cuts
default 
defaultand is
default potentially pejorative, conditional, subjective and can become int
defaultrusive.  In one instance our 
defaultlocal authority r
defaultefused
default a DHP claim because the 
defaultapplicant paid 
defaultfor dental insurance
default.  T
defaulthe tenant in question has very bad teeth as a result of a medical condition.  Another DHP was refused for 
defaulta wheelchair user, seeking work, t
defaulthey were relying on 
defaultbroadband in order to do this but it was deemed that broadband was an unnecessary ‘luxury’. The overall effect on our tenants could be that they become demonised and treated less favourably for attempting to improve their quality of life. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe anticipate that it is the most vulnerable groups, such as homeless households and households with a 
defaultdisability who
default will suffer the most.  Disabled households are the most difficult to transfer as the options open to them that are open to other tenants, su
defaultch as returning to work or the occasional
default opportunity to downsize
default are more limited.  They will often 
defaulthave no option but to find
default the shortfall or face eviction. 
defaultT
defaulthe total cost to the pub
defaultl
defaultic purse, sh
defaultould they be evicted, 
defaultis believed to be in the region of £7,000. 
